description:
&lt;p&gt;The Occupational Therapy service at Lincoln County Hospital provides a service to people in hospital who are experiencing difficulties with occupational performance. The focus of intervention is to promote individuals’ independence, choice and dignity whilst in hospital and upon their return home. The post holder will be responsible for the rapid assessment and facilitation of discharge to either the persons home or further place of rehabilitation. The post holder will work as part of the acute medical team covering a broad range of clinical areas including, cardiology, respiratory care, medical admissions unit, complex care &amp; oncology. The medical team is a well established &amp; dynamic friendly team consisting of bands 2-7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Friendly and supportive employment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strong and positive emphasis on multi-disciplinary working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plenty of opportunities for you to further your formal learning beyond registration including up to Masters Level study&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Teaching Opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consideration of your flexible working requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On-site accommodation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support with your special interests whether that is clinical or managerial&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a service we are committed to excellence and provide regular staff supervision and appraisal. The department regularly takes occupational therapy students from Sheffield Hallam and Derby University as well as from further afield. We also actively support those seeking work experience to pursue a career in Occupational Therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
